Experiment 1: Basic Pipeline with Parameter and BAT Command
Objective: To verify GitHub integration, parameter handling, and execution of simple Windows
batch commands using Jenkins Pipeline.
Version 1
• Task 1: Configure pipeline to checkout source code from GitHub repository.
• Task 2: Define a string parameter named MESSAGE and print its value in the console output.
• Task 3: Execute a simple Windows batch command using BAT to display 'Hello from Jenkins'.
Version 2
• Task 1: Checkout updated code from GitHub after modifying a file in IDE.
• Task 2: Execute BAT command to display current system date.
• Task 3: Print the parameter value again to verify parameter passing.
Version 3
• Task 1: Checkout latest commit from GitHub.
• Task 2: Create a file named output.txt using BAT command.
• Task 3: Display the contents of output.txt in Jenkins console.
Version 4
• Task 1: Checkout latest version from GitHub.
• Task 2: Accept USERNAME parameter from user.
• Task 3: Create user.txt file and store the username inside it.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
